      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755021559645,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Not dist/index.js as\nafter compilation by\ntsc the root dir will\nbe dist -> ./",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "DD4bjfoBc73tGCmrliqYI",
      "originalText": "Not dist/index.js as after compilation by tsc the root dir will be dist -> ./",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "tjTVWckQkug3NKwHd3LdK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -41.12517644857513,
      "y": 1802.375297440916,
      "width": 1030.779296875,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aR",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1344102588,
      "version": 544,
      "versionNonce": 1138153860,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755028781140,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "As if u write changes in code, the we need to stop docker running container then build the \nwhole specific service if written one in docker-compose, but to avoid this, we can use volumes\nso to put the files exact copy in it and if changes some code, it should able to track those changes\nand only copy those files to the container so the build process will be faster as we are going to use only\nfiles from docker volumes.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "As if u write changes in code, the we need to stop docker running container then build the \nwhole specific service if written one in docker-compose, but to avoid this, we can use volumes\nso to put the files exact copy in it and if changes some code, it should able to track those changes\nand only copy those files to the container so the build process will be faster as we are going to use only\nfiles from docker volumes.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8lEZPVl7NwSK7ze3SPfYf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -37.70976171176687,
      "y": 2037.069170157356,
      "width": 910.3994140625,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aS",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 813620807,
      "version": 118,
      "versionNonce": 1167836681,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755060203807,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker compose up\ndocker compose up --build -> rebuild container so that it also take changes in file we did now",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker compose up\ndocker compose up --build -> rebuild container so that it also take changes in file we did now",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "KSXh8v7KkmfdVYWuBPwJP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1.7543243277001466,
      "y": 2152.3109566447497,
      "width": 729.5994873046875,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 723002471,
      "version": 80,
      "versionNonce": 2039201607,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755060467937,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When exporting postman -> use .json extension as its not default, type it.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When exporting postman -> use .json extension as its not default, type it.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "iry4B_sTTSy2UGcYIXlsy",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -20.193010165683063,
      "y": 2227.9095685804796,
      "width": 1036.119140625,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aU",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 697983943,
      "version": 258,
      "versionNonce": 444785577,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755060805393,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "when u make changes in file, it auto reload the container show reflected changes as i am using ts-node-de\nbut if it dosen't then use --poll in the dev script in pkg.json after \"dev\":\"ts-node-dev --poll --files\"",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "when u make changes in file, it auto reload the container show reflected changes as i am using ts-node-de\nbut if it dosen't then use --poll in the dev script in pkg.json after \"dev\":\"ts-node-dev --poll --files\"",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
